<item>
            <title>[LU-9017] conf-sanity test_50d: lazystatfs failed with one down server</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9017</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Saurabh Tandan &amp;lt;saurabh.tandan@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/0dfb444e-d597-11e6-aa56-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/0dfb444e-d597-11e6-aa56-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_50d failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lazystatfs failed with one down server
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_logs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Commit the device label on lustre-ost2/ost2
CMD: onyx-43vm8 sync; sync; sync
CMD: onyx-43vm8 zfs get -H -o value lustre:svname 		                           lustre-ost2/ost2 2&amp;gt;/dev/null
Started lustre-OST0001
mount lustre on /mnt/lustre.....
Starting client: onyx-43vm1.onyx.hpdd.intel.com:  -o user_xattr,flock onyx-43vm7@tcp:/lustre /mnt/lustre
CMD: onyx-43vm1.onyx.hpdd.intel.com mkdir -p /mnt/lustre
CMD: onyx-43vm1.onyx.hpdd.intel.com mount -t lustre -o user_xattr,flock onyx-43vm7@tcp:/lustre /mnt/lustre
llite.lustre-ffff88007b016000.lazystatfs=1
stop ost1 service on onyx-43vm8
CMD: onyx-43vm8 grep -c /mnt/lustre-ost1&apos; &apos; /proc/mounts
Stopping /mnt/lustre-ost1 (opts:-f) on onyx-43vm8
CMD: onyx-43vm8 umount -d -f /mnt/lustre-ost1
CMD: onyx-43vm8 lsmod | grep lnet &amp;gt; /dev/null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; lctl dl | grep &apos; ST &apos;
CMD: onyx-43vm8 ! zpool list -H lustre-ost1 &amp;gt;/dev/null 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;1 ||
			grep -q ^lustre-ost1/ /proc/mounts ||
			zpool export  lustre-ost1
multiop /mnt/lustre vf_
TMPPIPE=/tmp/multiop_open_wait_pipe.3162
UUID                   1K-blocks        Used   Available Use% Mounted on
lustre-MDT0000_UUID      3007616        1664     3003904   0% /mnt/lustre[MDT:0]
lazystatfs df failed
/usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh: line 441: 15194 Killed                  $LFS df
 conf-sanity test_50d: @@@@@@ FAIL: lazystatfs failed with one down server 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
